cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with a problem in visual computing systems, specifically the removal of reflections from a single image captured through a glass window. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of neural network pipelines, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of misaligned data, which can be considered a form of data augmentation, and the use of context encoding modules, which can be considered a form of network enhancement. These topics fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which can be considered a form of performance evaluation, falling under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
